originalText.text: Daisy and her team at Sprouts are amazing!!! Our daughter is always so happy to go. They take incredible care of her-from feeding her delicious food, taking her to the park/playground, engaging her in developmentally appropriate activities to making her feel special and incredibly loved. We truly feel like we have won the lottery by having Daisy care for her and could not be happier. The Sprouts team care for her as if she is their own and and it is so evident in the smiles and excitement we see whenever she goes!

originalText.text: Sprouts has been amazing.  Our daughter has gone since she was 4 months old.  It is a safe and loving small group environment.  We feel so lucky to have found Daisy. Besides the camera, she cooks breakfast and lunch for them, even provides a snack.  They go outside as often as they can, and overall we could not be happier with Sprouts daycare.

originalText.text: We absolutely love Sprouts and are lucky to have found it!! My son has been going for more than a year and a half and is always excited to see the teachers and his friends. It is a small daycare and the teacher to student ratio is much better than the bigger Childcare centers we looked into. The teachers care so much for the children and make sure they are safe and healthy. It feels like we are dropping him off with family and he gets to socialize with kids of different ages each day. There is structured learning time in addition to the play time. My son has learned so much! I am constantly being told how good his counting and language is for his age, and I know a huge part of that is Sprouts!

originalText.text: Sprouts is a home away from home for our son. They are an extension of our family for our son and it truly feels like a partnership when it comes to our son’s development and happiness. The owner and staff are very courteous and nurturing. Our son started there at 5months and graduating at 3. They always pay attention to my son’s needs and change / introduce new activities to keep him engaged. We love Sprouts!

originalText.text: My Daughter started at Sprouts in 2019 for Afterschool Care. I cannot begin to say how much not only I love Sprouts and the staff but how much my daughter loves attending for afterschool. The owner Daisy is Amazing, she has great communication with parents and always there to help and answer any questions I might have. I have always went to work in peace knowing my daughter was being picked up from school by one of the Amazing ladies at Sprouts. Not only she got a snack afterschool, she also got dinner and help with homework, How amazing is that. When COVID-19 happen my daughter was so sad she wasn't able to attend daycare, see her daycare friends. But luckily we were able to go back and do Remote Learning from Daycare. And Sprouts was more than Amazing and so helpful with Remote learning! So happy I found them when I did. Let me also say how Sprouts Daycare is so clean always. They are always washing hands, sanitizing toys, tables, chairs. & this has always been like this even before COVID-19. I'm so happy I found Sprouts Daycare to care for my daughter.
